# Sequential equivalence — the shared tactic for every clean single-clock FSM proven by
# yosys-native SEC (AGENT.md §6). Driven by Yosys_equiv.run_proof; per-unit data is filled
# from the sequential/behavioral rows in formal_run.ml. Placeholders (named WITHOUT braces
# here on purpose — substitution is blind and would splice a value into this comment):
#   rtl      reference .v (rtl_dir for the Wirth originals, spec_dir for registers_spec.v)
#   ours/gate  our emitted Verilog + its module name (both harness-supplied)
#   top      reference top module
#   renames  a cd/rename block aligning our register names to the RTL's ("" when they match)
# equiv_make pairs flip-flops by name (after renames), equiv_induct proves the step by
# temporal induction, equiv_status -assert fails iff any $equiv is left open.
read_verilog {rtl}
read_verilog {ours}
proc
{renames}
# lower any $mem (ps2's fifo, the register-file array) to FFs so equiv_make pairs the memory
# state by name; a no-op for the memory-less iterative units
memory
opt
equiv_make {top} {gate} equiv
hierarchy -top equiv
opt -full
equiv_simple
equiv_induct
equiv_status -assert
